1
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:02,760
Water

2
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:16,040
Zhang Wei

3
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:17,040
Aren't you scared at all?

4
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:20,880
Water

5
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:22,080
What's there to be scared of?

6
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:23,040
She won't last more than a couple days.

7
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:24,960
In a couple days,

8
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:26,720
you and I can finally be together forever.

9
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,800
Oh, you're terrible.

10
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,440
Xiaofang

11
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:32,480
Let's not have our next date at the shop, okay?

12
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:33,320
This place of yours...

13
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:34,560
It's pretty creepy.

14
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:36,320
What?

15
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:37,640
Just like your dad,

16
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:38,880
you look down on our line of work?

17
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:41,120
Of course not!

18
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,120
My sweetie,

19
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:43,920
just say the word,

20
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:46,080
and I'll come work here with you right away.

21
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:48,200
I'll be at your beck and call.

22
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:52,960
Forget it.

23
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,400
You're too high-maintenance for me.

24
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:56,880
How did I get so high-maintenance?

25
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:58,480
Oh, right.

26
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,160
Next week, why don't we

27
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:02,160
go register our marriage first? How about it?

28
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:03,840
Can you keep your word?

29
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:05,000
Has your dad agreed?

30
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,400
Of course my word counts.

31
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,040
Auntie Huilan,

32
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:15,000
what are you doing here?

33
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,680
This is my boyfriend, Zhou Fang.

34
00:04:21,840 --> 00:04:22,920
This is Yiran's mom.

35
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,680
Hello, Auntie Huilan.

36
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:26,600
My name is...

37
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,040
Your name is Zhou Fang.

38
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,520
Didn't she just say it?

39
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:33,360
I need to cut in line.

40
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:36,280
I need to talk to Xiaofang about something.

41
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:39,680
Tonight, I need an answer, no matter what.

42
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,160
An answer to what?

43
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,480
Can't you take a hint?

44
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:47,560
Auntie Huilan means she wants you to get lost.

45
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:48,240
Now scram!

46
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,080
Fine.

47
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,080
Then go ahead and cut in line.

48
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:53,440
Get your answer first.

49
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,200
Xiaofang

50
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:14,280
I came to see you today

51
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,560
because I wanted you to tell me

52
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:21,360
about what Yiran's been through all these years

53
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,080
Where do I even start?

54
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:31,800
Well, anyway...

55
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:33,920
Right after you went in

56
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:37,760
Yiran and I were both bullied constantly

57
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:39,920
Everyone called her

58
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:41,240
a little murderer

59
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,160
One makes a living off the dead,

60
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,360
the other's a murderer

61
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:49,120
You two are really

62
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,040
a match made in heaven

63
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:56,040
Look at the state of her!

64
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,920
Later on

65
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:03,120
she went off to college in Shanghai

66
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:06,840
For years she refused to come back to Lecang

67
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:10,000
I keep thinking

68
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:13,320
maybe it's this place

69
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:15,160
that hurt her so deeply

70
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,840
During those years

71
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:23,880
she worked several jobs to support herself

72
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:30,520
Mom, this is Shanghai

73
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:33,600
Five thousand a month is nowhere near enough

74
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,800
Li Yiran, working her way through school

75
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:39,960
Hello

76
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:41,240
Here are your coffees

77
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:42,840
Yiran

78
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:44,160
We're heading to a bar in a bit

79
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:44,840
You coming?

80
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:47,200
I'll pass

81
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,160
Enjoy your drinks

82
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:51,240
Working stiff

83
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,640
Why bother asking her?

84
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,800
Country bumpkin

85
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,640
Get out of the way

86
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:56,760
Forget it

87
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:58,240
Let's not invite her next time

88
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,400
Such a buzzkill

89
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:31,800
Auntie Huilan

90
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,680
All the years you were gone

91
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:37,240
she's really had it rough

92
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:42,920
It's my fault

93
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:47,880
I wasn't a good mother

94
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:50,320
I didn't protect her

95
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,560
Auntie Huilan, don't say that

96
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:55,080
So it's normal she ignores me now

97
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:57,520
All that was so long ago

98
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:00,320
What happened next?

99
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,760
Well, later on

100
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:06,400
she graduated, right?

101
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:09,800
And she was about to settle in Shanghai

102
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,600
But recently that jerk cheated on her

103
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,800
What happened?

104
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:20,200
She's got no figure

105
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,880
and no money

106
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,640
The moment I got back, I dumped her

107
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:26,920
I hadn't wanted to see her for ages

108
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,840
And then after that

109
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,480
she just quit her job

110
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:32,880
If you ask me

111
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:34,840
That scumbag cheated with her boss

112
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:36,320
so why on earth should she quit?

113
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:40,360
She just can't stand any wrongdoing

114
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:44,680
Do you have that scumbag's phone number?

115
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:45,600
His address?

116
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:48,520
Tell me. This mama's going to Shanghai to fix him

117
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:50,200
Auntie Huilan, don't worry

118
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:52,200
Yiran sorted them out right on the spot

119
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,040
It was so satisfying

120
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:54,520
Really?

121
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:55,840
Really

122
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,200
Well done

123
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:06,200
Just like her mama

124
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,440
Otherwise this mama would've been furious

125
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:10,840
You can rest completely easy, Auntie Huilan

126
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:12,640
Yiran's just stubborn with her words

127
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,080
Deep down she cares about you a lot

128
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:16,320
Really?

129
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:17,080
Really

130
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,320
She really cares about me?

131
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,720
She absolutely cares about you

132
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,320
Then if...

133
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,360
Auntie Huilan

134
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,640
Did you get your answer?

135
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:32,720
How about

136
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,400
you let me cut in line first

137
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:36,400
I want an answer too

138
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:38,880
Your name's Zhou Fang

139
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:42,000
You'll never get your answer in this lifetime

140
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,680
You'll never hold on to Xiaofang

141
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:53,320
Auntie Huilan, why are you cursing me?

142
00:09:58,280 --> 00:09:59,520
Xiaofang

143
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:02,280
Then let's go get our marriage license next week

144
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,720
Yiran

145
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:20,400
What made you come wash your hair here today?

146
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:23,000
Our water's cut off at home

147
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:25,480
Had hot pot yesterday, my hair reeks of it

148
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:26,480
It's driving me crazy

149
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,160
Mom

150
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:30,560
Yaya got loose, I can't catch her

151
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:33,200
Yaya got loose

152
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:34,560
That darn bird

153
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:36,240
Yiran, wait a sec, I'll be right back

154
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:37,400
Honestly

155
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:38,520
Where is it now?

156
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,000
Auntie Juan

157
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:52,640
Yangyang

158
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:56,520
I totally forgot about this

159
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,000
Auntie Juan

160
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,120
Auntie Juan

161
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,200
I'm back, Auntie Juan

162
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:14,720
Did you catch Yaya?

163
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,080
What are you doing here?

164
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:42,280
So many bubbles.

165
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:44,840
Sleep well, sleep well.

166
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:51,960
Just close your eyes.

167
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:20,960
How's the pressure?

168
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:23,960
Fine, just hurry up and wash it.

169
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:24,880
Just rinse it off for me.

170
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:13,160
Okay, okay, okay.

171
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:15,200
Peanuts and beer, coming right up!

172
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:18,960
Here.

173
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,640
Here's your glass.

174
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:38,040
This one I'm grilling here,

175
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:39,960
it's called Hearts Connected.

176
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:42,160
There's no hurdle we can't get over.

177
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:44,560
We're always a family with hearts connected.

178
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:45,560
Exactly.

179
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:47,640
Yiran, Lan, eat while it's hot.

180
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:48,680
Daren's treating today.

181
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,200
I run a small business, you know.

182
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:53,040
I really can't afford to treat.

183
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:55,400
My treat, my treat, my treat.

184
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:56,720
I'm not eating.

185
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:58,320
Yiran, Yiran, Yiran.

186
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,000
My treat, my treat.

187
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:02,560
Everything on the table tonight,

188
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:03,480
it's my treat.

189
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,560
Don't be shy.

190
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:05,520
Sit, sit, sit.

191
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:09,440
Okay, I'll go grill some more.

192
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,000
Weren't you not eating?

193
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:16,920
So why'd you sit back down?

194
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:19,960
Uncle Daren's the one treating.

195
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:21,000
Am I eating your food?

196
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:22,200
Is it any of your business?

197
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:24,680
You're the egg I hatched.

198
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:26,600
If I didn't look out for you,

199
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:28,440
you'd have been smashed to bits long ago.

200
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:31,600
Um...

201
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,640
Auntie Huilan meant well, after all.

202
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:35,800
At least she got us some payback, right?

203
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:38,240
Yiran, cut her some slack too.

204
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,640
Cut her slack for what?

205
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:41,320
Does cutting her slack even help?

206
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:43,280
She still won't listen either way.

207
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:44,720
Troublemaker.

208
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:51,800
I was wrong, okay?

209
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,160
I admit I was wrong, isn't that enough?

210
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:56,440
They'll be my witnesses today.

211
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:59,040
I'll never cause trouble again.

212
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:00,120
I mean it.

213
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,200
Yeah right, like I'd believe you.

214
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:03,600
Zhang Lijuan.

215
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:06,640
Scam call.

216
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:08,440
Go on, go on.

217
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:11,920
Talk is cheap, you know.

218
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,400
So what do you want, then?

219
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:19,320
Let's put it in writing.

220
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:27,400
So you came prepared, huh.

221
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:29,520
Then I'll have to think it over carefully.

222
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:30,800
Are you signing or not?

223
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:31,560
Forget it if you won't.

224
00:15:31,560 --> 00:15:32,560
I knew you never meant to change.

225
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,000
I'll sign, I'll sign.

226
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:35,640
I'll sign, I'll sign.

227
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:36,600
I don't have a pen.

228
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:42,080
Look, here's a pen for you.

229
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:43,920
Here's your pen.

230
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:48,120
This mama's stuck being Party B.

231
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:01,400
There, you satisfied now?

232
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:03,440
No, I'm not.

233
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:05,440
What else could you possibly want?

234
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:07,320
This mama, all her life,

235
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:08,800
has never written a single guarantee.

236
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:11,160
Do you even have a job right now?

237
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,480
Being jobless isn't the problem, Huilan.

238
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:15,680
The problem is you never keep one.

239
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,920
I know. I'll find a job.

240
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:20,400
Don't you worry.

241
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:22,440
I won't make you support me in old age.

242
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:23,960
I can earn my own money.

243
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:25,360
You'd better.

244
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:38,920
Let's make a toast

245
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:39,640
Come on

246
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:40,320
Come on, come on

247
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:41,520
Here we go

248
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:42,480
Have a drink, have a drink

249
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:46,320
Come on, Yiran

250
00:16:56,040 --> 00:16:57,440
Normally

251
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:59,000
I'd be drinking till I drop tonight

252
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:02,040
But

253
00:17:02,040 --> 00:17:04,080
since I promised Li Yiran

254
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:06,200
that I'd cut back on drinking

255
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:08,320
I'll only have one glass

256
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:11,800
Just one, just one

257
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:14,600
Alright

258
00:17:15,120 --> 00:17:16,240
Just one glass then

259
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:31,360
Won't you have a drink?

260
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,800
This one's for you.

261
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:35,720
Are you crazy, Wu Huilan?

262
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:39,080
Your wounds aren't even healed and you're drinking?

263
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:40,680
What do you know?

264
00:17:41,520 --> 00:17:43,200
This is called drowning my sorrows.

265
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:44,200
Fighting poison with poison.

266
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:53,320
Come on.

267
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,000
Let's have a drink.

268
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:57,760
And to celebrate Yiran coming back, right?

269
00:17:58,520 --> 00:17:59,360
Come on, come on.

270
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:00,000
Come on, come on.

271
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:03,320
Come on, come on.

272
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,200
Cheers, cheers!

273
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:17,000
Zhang Lijuan.

274
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:18,120
You have no idea.

275
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:20,520
I was so badass that day.

276
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:21,400
What happened?

277
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:22,720
That scumbag

278
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:24,960
came to Paradise Funeral Home to hassle Yiran.

279
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:27,120
This mama grabbed a brick and charged right at him.

280
00:18:30,040 --> 00:18:30,800
And then?

281
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:33,120
Then she ran over and blocked me.

282
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:36,840
But I found my second chance.

283
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:38,840
This mama grabbed the brick and smacked again.

284
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:40,760
And then?

285
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:44,120
And I smacked it right on my own head.

286
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:47,160
But only a little blood came out.

287
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:48,600
Not that much blood.

288
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:50,640
The key thing is,

289
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:54,000
I turned that brick around

290
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:56,120
and put it in that scumbag's hand.

291
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:58,520
So when we got to the police station,

292
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:01,080
the cops couldn't do a thing to me.

293
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:02,760
Because that brick

294
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:04,680
was covered in his fingerprints.

295
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:07,080
So tell me, isn't this head of mine clever?

296
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:09,960
So clever!

297
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:11,120
Sis Lan.

298
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:12,400
To your cleverness,

299
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:13,160
let's have one.

300
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:14,000
Have one.

301
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:21,520
A couple of drinks and she's bragging again.

302
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:45,320
I can't take it anymore

303
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:47,200
Why did you drink it all?

304
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,000
I promised you

305
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:58,400
Just one glass

306
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:00,800
I keep my word

307
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:06,240
Come on, let's hit the restroom

308
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:07,240
Come on

309
00:21:10,760 --> 00:21:11,600
Wu Huilan

310
00:21:14,960 --> 00:21:16,960
No more overthinking

311
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:27,840
When your heart is big

312
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:31,200
your problems become small

313
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,840
It's really no big deal

314
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:39,960
Right, Lao Li?

315
00:21:43,960 --> 00:21:44,840
Don't you worry

316
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:49,400
I'll never do anything foolish

317
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:54,000
I still want to be there for our Yiran

318
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:57,600
I'll listen to her

319
00:22:00,280 --> 00:22:01,960
Find myself a good job

320
00:22:01,960 --> 00:22:02,920
Not be a burden to her

321
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:13,240
I've got to stay strong

322
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:23,200
Stay strong

323
00:22:34,840 --> 00:22:35,640
Here.

324
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:43,200
Yiran.

325
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:46,680
There's actually something I've wanted to ask you.

326
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:49,520
Go ahead and ask.

327
00:22:50,280 --> 00:22:53,760
How could you tell those two were having an affair?

328
00:22:53,760 --> 00:22:55,400
You don't even know them.

329
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:04,760
I...

330
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:07,120
I've always been a

331
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:09,720
materialist who doesn't believe in ghosts or gods.

332
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:11,560
I figured in this world,

333
00:23:11,560 --> 00:23:13,960
there's no such thing as all that mystical stuff.

334
00:23:13,960 --> 00:23:16,120
But the day of the old man's funeral,

335
00:23:16,640 --> 00:23:19,040
the moment I touched his belongings,

336
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:21,280
I got Sensory Resonance.

337
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:23,640
I could see and hear

338
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:25,720
things that happened while he was alive.

339
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:27,240
Just like a dream.

340
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:41,400
Yiran

341
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:46,840
This is your dad's phone

342
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:50,200
The police finished their exam and sent it over

343
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:20,480
Ever since I hit my head that night

344
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:21,960
I've been having nightmares all the time

345
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:24,360
Maybe it's from too much grief

346
00:26:24,360 --> 00:26:26,240
causing hallucinations and after-effects

347
00:26:27,280 --> 00:26:28,880
Hey, hey

348
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:31,560
I'm talking to you

349
00:26:31,560 --> 00:26:33,240
Zoning out again, are you?

350
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:35,720
Didn't you say it yourself?

351
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:37,960
I'm the Reincarnation of Sun Wukong

352
00:26:37,960 --> 00:26:39,680
I've got the Eyes of truth

353
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:41,440
And you actually believed me?

354
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:46,040
If you ask me, that was just Blind luck

355
00:26:46,360 --> 00:26:47,640
Pure Dumb luck

356
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:50,320
If This mama had any dumb luck

357
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:51,840
I'd be in Shanghai right now

358
00:26:51,840 --> 00:26:53,160
making a name for myself

359
00:26:57,360 --> 00:26:58,160
Yiran

360
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:02,000
There's something I'm not sure

361
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:03,320
whether I should say or not

362
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:05,080
If you shouldn't, then don't

363
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:12,240
Life, you know

364
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:15,960
just forget about the past

365
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:19,040
What truly matters

366
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:22,720
is only the present

367
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:57,960
We don't offer a base salary here

368
00:27:57,960 --> 00:27:58,880
And no social security either

369
00:27:58,880 --> 00:27:59,840
It's commission per item

370
00:27:59,840 --> 00:28:01,400
You sell one, you earn on that one

371
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:02,200
Can you accept that?

372
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:03,360
Yes, I can accept that

373
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:04,120
I can accept it

374
00:28:04,440 --> 00:28:06,440
So when can I start work?

375
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:07,880
This is my ID card

376
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:10,120
Born in '78

377
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:11,080
Year of the Horse

378
00:28:12,040 --> 00:28:12,880
I'm Year of the Rat

379
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:13,920
Our birth signs clash

380
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:14,480
Off you go, now

381
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:15,720
Go on, hurry

382
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:16,880
Don't hold up my business, all right?

383
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:20,440
We sometimes do unpaid overtime here

384
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:21,360
Is that okay?

385
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:22,320
Unpaid, mind you

386
00:28:23,680 --> 00:28:26,080
Sure, overtime's no problem

387
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:29,040
But isn't Yiwu a bit far for overtime?

388
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:31,840
Is there travel pay? Overtime pay?

389
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:33,560
I said unpaid overtime

390
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:35,080
Not that you fly to Yiwu

391
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:37,080
This one's not right in the head

392
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:37,720
Off you go, go on, go

393
00:28:38,480 --> 00:28:40,880
Go, go, go, I don't dare hire you

394
00:28:40,880 --> 00:28:42,240
You've killed someone

395
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:43,920
It was excessive self-defense

396
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:45,640
Excessive self-defense is still killing

397
00:28:45,840 --> 00:28:46,800
Go, go, go

398
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:47,880
Go, go, go

399
00:28:48,760 --> 00:28:49,680
I don't dare hire you

400
00:28:49,680 --> 00:28:50,680
Don't come any closer!

401
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:10,400
You... you're thirty-three?

402
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:13,360
Yeah, I'm thirty-three.

403
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:14,400
I'm from the countryside, so I look older.

404
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:16,800
Alright, everyone, listen up.

405
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:17,760
We've got way too many people

406
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:19,320
here today.

407
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:21,360
Anyone over thirty-five,

408
00:29:21,360 --> 00:29:22,960
you can head home now.

409
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:25,200
Also, for the women here,

410
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:26,960
if you're married with kids,

411
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:29,040
you can step out and go home too.

412
00:29:30,880 --> 00:29:32,000
Come on, keep up back there.

413
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:33,200
Don't break the line.

414
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:35,440
Pick up the pace, come on.

415
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:40,560
We're keeping things strict over here.

416
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:41,520
Just like I said before.

417
00:29:41,520 --> 00:29:42,760
We're not short on people today.

418
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:44,440
We're mainly filtering, okay?

419
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:45,480
Right, we want quality.

420
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:33,280
How'd it go?

421
00:30:37,720 --> 00:30:39,480
I'm exhausted.

422
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:50,160
I knew it.

423
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:52,520
This mama definitely didn't check the almanac today.

424
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:53,880
Inauspicious day for everything.

425
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:57,360
You blame the heavens, the earth, the almanac.

426
00:30:57,720 --> 00:30:59,480
Didn't I teach you some interview lines?

427
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:00,640
How could it not work?

428
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:03,000
What are you so anxious about?

429
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:05,120
What's that supposed to mean?

430
00:31:05,600 --> 00:31:07,240
Are you itching to get back to Shanghai?

431
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:09,360
Then go on back.

432
00:31:09,640 --> 00:31:11,120
I don't need you keeping me company.

433
00:31:11,120 --> 00:31:12,760
This mama will stay and take her time job-hunting.

434
00:31:12,760 --> 00:31:15,160
Fine, I'll go! I'm heading back to Shanghai tomorrow.

435
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:16,840
I get along just fine on my own in Shanghai.

436
00:31:17,760 --> 00:31:19,120
This mama gets along just fine too.

437
00:31:19,320 --> 00:31:20,880
Who wants to be around you anyway?

438
00:31:42,360 --> 00:31:43,520
Heavenly spirits turn,

439
00:31:44,240 --> 00:31:45,480
earthly demons hide.

440
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:47,360
Fortune and misfortune,

441
00:31:47,520 --> 00:31:48,640
set by yin and yang.

442
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:51,480
The compass points,

443
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:53,000
the aura rises.

444
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:54,920
Evil spirits and bad luck

445
00:31:55,080 --> 00:31:56,320
have nowhere to hide.

446
00:31:58,200 --> 00:31:59,720
What kind of nonsense is this?

447
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:02,800
Hired a master to clear your mom's bad luck.

448
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:04,320
Right, so don't cause any trouble.

449
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:06,280
The master is reading our feng shui.

450
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:10,040
Master, how's the feng shui in our home?

451
00:32:10,560 --> 00:32:11,760
The stove faces west.

452
00:32:12,040 --> 00:32:13,560
Fire overcomes metal.

453
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:14,920
A sign of financial loss.

454
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:16,840
Wu Huilan,

455
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:18,400
you're someone who has to sneak

456
00:32:18,400 --> 00:32:20,080
onto the bus with someone's senior card,

457
00:32:20,080 --> 00:32:21,400
and you believe this con man's garbage?

458
00:32:25,080 --> 00:32:26,000
Watch your mouth.

459
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:27,480
That master is really accurate, you know.

460
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:29,440
One yin, two yang,

461
00:32:29,440 --> 00:32:30,840
Three Pure Ones, Four Emperors,

462
00:32:30,840 --> 00:32:32,280
disasters and calamities,

463
00:32:32,280 --> 00:32:33,880
all shaped by human effort.

464
00:32:35,040 --> 00:32:36,440
By divine command!

465
00:32:44,520 --> 00:32:46,760
Master, why are you sighing like that?

466
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:47,560
What's wrong?

467
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:48,640
Patron Wu,

468
00:32:49,280 --> 00:32:52,000
this hexagram signals an Industry Jinx.

469
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:53,760
Disaster is coming.

470
00:32:54,160 --> 00:32:54,760
When it does,

471
00:32:54,760 --> 00:32:57,960
your home will be in chaos, all lost.

472
00:32:59,240 --> 00:33:00,440
So what do we do?

473
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:02,840
Pay up.

474
00:33:09,600 --> 00:33:11,000
The master will cast a spell.

475
00:33:14,880 --> 00:33:15,960
Thank you, Master.

476
00:33:18,840 --> 00:33:19,640
Patron Wu,

477
00:33:20,560 --> 00:33:21,720
this curse is hard to break.

478
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:25,120
Spend money to avert disaster.

479
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:25,920
Give it all.

480
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:26,680
Give it all!

481
00:33:28,360 --> 00:33:29,440
I've got some more here.

482
00:33:33,280 --> 00:33:34,920
This is all of it, Master.

483
00:33:34,920 --> 00:33:35,680
Nothing left.

484
00:33:37,560 --> 00:33:38,600
Sincerity is arriving.

485
00:33:43,040 --> 00:33:45,080
Look, look, he's casting the spell!

486
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:48,240
One yin, two yang, Three Pure Ones, Four Emperors,

487
00:33:48,480 --> 00:33:49,720
disasters and calamities,

488
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:51,120
all shaped by human effort.

489
00:33:56,920 --> 00:33:59,480
Wind, fire, thunder, lightning,

490
00:33:59,480 --> 00:34:00,320
break!

491
00:34:01,720 --> 00:34:02,880
What's he doing?

492
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:04,120
Casting the spell, casting the spell!

493
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:10,280
Wind, fire, thunder, lightning,

494
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:10,920
break!

495
00:34:15,160 --> 00:34:16,840
Look, look, he's casting the spell!

496
00:34:22,840 --> 00:34:23,960
The candle lit up!

497
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:25,040
That's amazing!

498
00:34:25,240 --> 00:34:25,960
Patron Wu,

499
00:34:27,240 --> 00:34:28,960
in the southeast corner of the room,

500
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:30,160
I've lit a candle

501
00:34:30,160 --> 00:34:31,120
and set up a formation.

502
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:32,880
When the candle dies on its own,

503
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:34,680
the disaster breaks by itself.

504
00:34:35,080 --> 00:34:36,560
So "the candle dies on its own" means

505
00:34:36,560 --> 00:34:38,280
we wait for it to go out by itself, right?

506
00:34:43,440 --> 00:34:45,360
Heaven's secrets cannot be revealed.

507
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:46,720
Farewell.

508
00:34:47,680 --> 00:34:49,040
Can't, can't let it go out.

509
00:34:49,440 --> 00:34:50,200
Thank you, Master.

510
00:34:50,200 --> 00:34:51,440
Here, Master, let me see you out.

511
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:52,560
Master, thank you for your hard work.

512
00:34:55,080 --> 00:34:56,480
Master, here, let me get the door for you.

513
00:34:56,800 --> 00:34:57,760
You know what?

514
00:34:58,240 --> 00:34:59,440
Now that the spell's been cast,

515
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:01,120
I'll find a job in no time.

516
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:02,760
Keep laughing at me, then.

517
00:35:04,680 --> 00:35:05,320
Master.

518
00:35:05,320 --> 00:35:06,720
Coming, coming, let me see you out.

519
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:16,280
Lighting a candle in the southeast corner?

520
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,720
Watched too much Ghost Blows Out the Light?

521
00:35:18,520 --> 00:35:19,840
It can't break on its own?

522
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:21,760
Then I'll break it myself.

523
00:35:32,240 --> 00:35:33,520
Plus 36 equals

524
00:35:33,520 --> 00:35:34,400
Plus

525
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:37,440
Eight equals 207

526
00:35:42,800 --> 00:35:43,960
Yiran

527
00:35:43,960 --> 00:35:44,880
Do me a favor, would you?

528
00:35:45,640 --> 00:35:46,560
If there are any job openings,

529
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:47,680
keep an eye out for me.

530
00:35:48,440 --> 00:35:49,520
Have you thought this through?

531
00:35:49,520 --> 00:35:50,120
You want to stay?

532
00:35:50,760 --> 00:35:52,880
Not me, it's Wu Huilan.

533
00:35:53,240 --> 00:35:55,240
She's going crazy looking for a job.

534
00:35:55,480 --> 00:35:57,120
She went to some fortune-teller, you know?

535
00:35:57,760 --> 00:35:59,680
Once she finds a stable job,

536
00:35:59,680 --> 00:36:00,880
I can go back to Shanghai.

537
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:02,520
If I keep hanging around here,

538
00:36:02,520 --> 00:36:04,040
my social security will lapse.

539
00:36:04,040 --> 00:36:05,480
Go back to Shanghai? What for?

540
00:36:05,480 --> 00:36:07,840
Just stay and work with me.

541
00:36:07,840 --> 00:36:08,840
Let me tell you,

542
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:10,040
with the silver economy now,

543
00:36:10,040 --> 00:36:11,520
funeral services is a sunrise industry.

544
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:13,040
Sisters united

545
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:14,240
are unstoppable.

546
00:36:14,240 --> 00:36:16,920
Let's grow Paradise Funeral Home together!

547
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:18,280
I'm not joking with you.

548
00:36:18,280 --> 00:36:19,520
I'm definitely going back to Shanghai.

549
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:22,160
Anyway, you've got so many connections.

550
00:36:22,560 --> 00:36:24,440
If there's a job, look out for her, okay?

551
00:36:26,520 --> 00:36:27,760
What a heavy rain!

552
00:36:32,560 --> 00:36:35,600
A job? Here one comes.

553
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:44,760
This Chen Xiaofang is so unreliable.

554
00:36:45,560 --> 00:36:47,080
What is there to do at a zoo?

555
00:36:48,320 --> 00:36:50,840
I think working here is pretty nice, actually.

556
00:36:50,840 --> 00:36:51,800
The air is fresh,

557
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:53,360
and you get to be with the little animals.

558
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:55,040
Plus there are so many cypress leaves.

559
00:36:55,520 --> 00:36:57,760
Grab a few to roast sausages, so tasty!

560
00:36:59,080 --> 00:36:59,880
Not bad.

561
00:37:13,240 --> 00:37:14,200
Run!

562
00:37:15,480 --> 00:37:18,080
Big bear! Big bear!

563
00:37:22,400 --> 00:37:23,200
Li Yiran

564
00:37:26,080 --> 00:37:28,160
Do you really not remember me,

565
00:37:28,160 --> 00:37:29,520
or are you just pretending?

566
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:33,640
Of course I remember you,

567
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:35,360
Miss Fan.

